<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:137931" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subSpecies="rufescens">var. rufescens Wasmann</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph>
- J'ai examine un assez grand nombre d'exemplaires de cette variete recus autrefois du Congo francais et du Cameroun, ainsi que les types que le R. P. Wasmann a bien voulu me communiquer. Ils me paraissent constituer une transition entre 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:149700" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subSpecies="burmeisteri">burmeisteri</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229219" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="sjoestedti">sjoestedti</taxonomicName>
. La sculpture assez mate et les cotes un peu arques de la tete chez les [[ soldier ]] rappellent la race 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:149703" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subSpecies="sjoestedti">sjoestedti</taxonomicName>
, mais ce sont la des caracteres assez inconstants, les plus grands exemplaires (11 mill.) ont une tendance a avoir le vertex et les cotes de la tete assez luisants, tandis qu'ils restent toujours opaques chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229219" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="sjoestedti">Sjoestedti</taxonomicName>
. D'autre part, la forme de la tete chez les ouvrieres de moyenne longueur (entre 6 et 7 mill.) reste, chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229226" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="rufescens">rufescens</taxonomicName>
, identique a celle des ouvrieres de toutes les varietes de la race 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229215" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="burmeisteri">burmeisteri</taxonomicName>
, c'est-a-dire bien plus large, plus courte, plus luisante et relativement plus robuste que chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:149703" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subSpecies="sjoestedti" subgenus="Anomma">sjoestedti</taxonomicName>
, de meme taille, le penultieme article du funicule a peine deux fois plus long qu'epais (trois fois chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229219" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="sjoestedti">sjoestedti</taxonomicName>
de 7 mill.). La forme du pedicule varie un peu: il est tantot aussi long que chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229219" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans sjoestedti Emery" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="sjoestedti">sjoestedti</taxonomicName>
, tantot comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229215" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="burmeisteri">burmeisteri</taxonomicName>
. Je rattache donc celte forme comme variete de a 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229215" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus nigricans burmeisteri (Shuckard)" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="burmeisteri">burmeisteri</taxonomicName>
. Du reste, j'ai sous les yeux toutes les transitions entre 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230638" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. rubella" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. rubella" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" variety="rubella">rubella</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229226" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="rufescens">rufescens</taxonomicName>
, parmi lesquelles je crois pouvoir distinguer une variete - 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229224" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. ornata" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. ornata" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="ornata">ornata</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="variety">n. var.</taxonomicNameLabel>
- qui rappelle 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229226" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus rufescens Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="rufescens">rufescens</taxonomicName>
par sa couleur et sa forme, mais dont la tete est luisante chez les individus de toutes tailles, comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230638" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. rubella" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. rubella" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" variety="rubella">rubella</taxonomicName>
. Je regarde comme type de la var. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:229224" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. ornata" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Dorylus (Anomma) nigricans subsp. ornata" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans" subGenus="Anomma" subSpecies="ornata">ornata</taxonomicName>
des exemplaires du Cameroun (communiques par M. Emery), dont la couleur rouge vif tranche nettement avec le noir des angles anterieurs de la tete.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
